From: hermes-agent <kernel@oneplus-nord-ce5>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 21:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 0006] mm/hybridswap: rebuild hs_swap when zram->disksize grew
 past the frozen nr_objs (root-cause fix for HYB_ZRAM "index invalid" flood)

ROOT CAUSE (verified on-device, OnePlus Nord CE5 / mt6897, OOS16):

The HYB_ZRAM log floods at boot with FOUR signatures that all cascade from
a SINGLE failed bounds check:

    hybridswap_zram_lru_add:3790 index = 2067925 invalid
    hybridswap_zram_lru_del:3810 index = ... invalid
    obj_idx:1398 idx = ... invalid
    get_obj_table_node:1443 idx = -22 invalid
    hs_list_get_mcgid:1147 idx = -22, table = 0000000000000000

Mechanism (one bug, not four):
  1. lru_add/del() and obj_idx() reject any zram slot index >= nr_objs and
     obj_idx() returns -EINVAL (-22).
  2. That -22 flows into get_obj_table_node(-22) -> idx < 0 -> NULL.
  3. idx_node(-22) == NULL -> hs_list_get_mcgid() logs "table = 0" and
     returns 0. So "table = 0000000000000000" is the propagated -22, NOT a
     NULL per-memcg oem_data table (this supersedes the premise of 0005).

Why nr_objs is short:
  * hs_swap->nr_objs is frozen as (ori_size >> PAGE_SHIFT) in
    alloc_hybridswap(), ori_size = zram->disksize captured when
    hybridswap_mgr_init() runs (driven by the hybridswap_core_enable sysfs
    write).
  * zram->table is sized in zram_meta_alloc() from the FINAL zram->disksize
    set by disksize_store().
  * On this device the enable fires while disksize is still ~7.5 GiB
    (nr_objs ~= 1.96M), then zram is reset (zram_reset_device() calls
    hybridswap_unbind() but NOT hybridswap_mgr_deinit(), so the stale
    hs_swap survives) and resized to the final 8 GiB (disksize>>12 =
    2097152 slots). The re-enable then hits the
    "if (hybridswap_core_enabled() || !en) return 0;" guard in
    hybridswap_set_enable_init() and never rebuilds hs_swap.
  * Result: zram hands out slot indices up to 2097151 while hs_swap still
    believes nr_objs ~= 1967786. Every slot in the gap is rejected -> the
    flood, and hybridswap silently refuses to track/reclaim those pages
    (the feature is half-broken, not merely noisy). Confirmed on-device:
    /sys/block/zram0/disksize = 8589934592 and the lowest rejected index
    in the logs (~1967786) is below 2097152.

FIX (root cause, not silencing):
  Make hs_swap sizing track the live zram->disksize.

  (a) hybridswap_mgr_init(): if a stale hs_swap already exists whose
      nr_objs does not match (zram->disksize >> PAGE_SHIFT), free it first
      so the following alloc_hybridswap() rebuilds it at the correct size.
      Makes mgr_init idempotent / self-healing.
  (b) hybridswap_set_enable_init(): relax the early-return guard so that
      when already enabled but the live disksize no longer matches the
      frozen nr_objs, we mgr_deinit + rebuild instead of returning 0.
      Steady-state (sizes match) keeps the original cheap early-return, so
      this is a no-op on every boot where the ordering was benign.

Both paths only act on a real size mismatch; no slot index is ever clamped
or silenced. KMI-safe: no new exported symbol, no struct layout change
(nr_objs/disksize are existing fields), module-internal only.

NOTE on 0005: it replayed android_vh_mem_cgroup_alloc to populate per-memcg
oem_data tables from the GKI side. Given the mechanism proven here, the
"table = 0" line is the propagated -22, not a NULL oem_data slot, so 0005
does not address this flood. 0005 is harmless (idempotent replay) and is
left in place; drop it separately once this patch is confirmed to clear the
logs.

Signed-off-by: hermes-agent <kernel@oneplus-nord-ce5>
---
diff --git a/vendor/oplus/kernel/mm/hybridswap_zram/hybridswap/hybridswap.c b/vendor/oplus/kernel/mm/hybridswap_zram/hybridswap/hybridswap.c
--- a/vendor/oplus/kernel/mm/hybridswap_zram/hybridswap/hybridswap.c
+++ b/vendor/oplus/kernel/mm/hybridswap_zram/hybridswap/hybridswap.c
@@ -2680,9 +2680,33 @@
 {
 	int ret;
 
-	if (hybridswap_core_enabled() || !en)
+	if (!en)
 		return 0;
 
+	/*
+	 * Self-healing re-enable: hybridswap may already be enabled with an
+	 * hs_swap whose nr_objs was frozen against an earlier (smaller)
+	 * zram->disksize -- e.g. enabled at ~7.5G, then zram reset and
+	 * resized to 8G without rebuilding the manager (zram_reset_device()
+	 * only unbinds, it does not mgr_deinit). In that case the object
+	 * table is too short and every slot index in the gap is rejected.
+	 * Detect the size mismatch and rebuild instead of early-returning.
+	 */
+	if (hybridswap_core_enabled()) {
+		struct zram *zram = global_settings.zram;
+
+		if (!zram || !zram->hs_swap)
+			return 0;
+		if ((int)(zram->disksize >> PAGE_SHIFT) == zram->hs_swap->nr_objs)
+			return 0;
+
+		log_info("disksize grew (nr_objs %d, disksize pages %lu); rebuilding hs_swap\n",
+			 zram->hs_swap->nr_objs,
+			 (unsigned long)(zram->disksize >> PAGE_SHIFT));
+		hybridswap_mgr_deinit(zram);
+		/* fall through to rebuild below */
+	}
+
 	if (!global_settings.stat) {
 		log_err("global_settings.stat is null!\n");
 
@@ -3606,6 +3630,23 @@
 		goto out;
 	}
 
+	/*
+	 * Idempotent / self-healing: if a stale hs_swap survives from an
+	 * earlier enable (its nr_objs was frozen against a smaller
+	 * disksize), free it so the alloc below rebuilds it sized to the
+	 * live zram->disksize. Without this the object table stays short
+	 * forever and zram slot indices beyond the old nr_objs are all
+	 * rejected (HYB_ZRAM "index invalid" flood + lost reclaim).
+	 */
+	if (zram->hs_swap &&
+	    zram->hs_swap->nr_objs != (int)(zram->disksize >> PAGE_SHIFT)) {
+		log_info("stale hs_swap nr_objs %d != disksize pages %lu; freeing for rebuild\n",
+			 zram->hs_swap->nr_objs,
+			 (unsigned long)(zram->disksize >> PAGE_SHIFT));
+		free_hybridswap(zram->hs_swap);
+		zram->hs_swap = NULL;
+	}
+
 	zram->hs_swap = alloc_hybridswap(zram->disksize,
 					 zram->nr_pages << PAGE_SHIFT);
 	if (!zram->hs_swap) {
